Package: aksStat
Type: Package
Title: Random Sampling and Cross-Validation Utilities for Statistical Learning
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Aubrey", "Schrameck",
      email = "aubreyschrameck@gmail.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: A collection of functions for sampling and validation in statistical learning. 
    Includes implementations of the inverse CDF method, accept-reject sampling, 
    Markov Chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) via the Metropolis algorithm, Gelman diagnostics, 
    and subset-based cross-validation with support for LDA, QDA, GLM, and KNN models.
